#. <section class="sutta" id="sn9.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga"
msgstr "1. In the Woods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn9.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Vivekasutta"
msgstr "1. Seclusion"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.197"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.424"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn9.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn9.1:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time one of the mendicants was staying in the land of the Kosalans in "
"a certain forest grove."

msgctxt "sn9.1:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena so bhikkhu divāvihāragato pāpake akusale vitakke "
"vitakketi gehanissite."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time that mendicant, during their day’s meditation, was thinking "
"bad, unskillful thoughts to do with the lay life."

msgctxt "sn9.1:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tassa bhikkhuno anukampikā "
"atthakāmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ saṃvejetukāmā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"The deity haunting that forest had compassion for that mendicant, and wanted "
"what’s best for them. So they approached that mendicant wanting to stir them "
"up, and addressed them in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.1:2.1"
msgid "“Vivekakāmosi vanaṃ paviṭṭho,"
msgstr "“You entered the woods desiring seclusion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:2.2"
msgid "Atha te mano niccharatī bahiddhā;"
msgstr "yet your mind wanders off to outward things."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:2.3"
msgid "Jano janasmiṃ vinayassu chandaṃ,"
msgstr "As a person, you should dispel the desire for people."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:2.4"
msgid "Tato sukhī hohisi vītarāgo."
msgstr "Then you’ll be happy, free of greed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.425"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.1:3.1"
msgid "Aratiṃ pajahāsi sato,"
msgstr "Mindful, give up discontent;"

# See BB.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:3.2"
msgid "Bhavāsi sataṃ taṃ sārayāmase;"
msgstr "let us remind you of the way of the good."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:3.3"
msgid "Pātālarajo hi duttaro,"
msgstr "The dusty abyss is so hard to cross;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:3.4"
msgid "Mā taṃ kāmarajo avāhari."
msgstr "don’t let sensual dust drag you down."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: paṃsukunthito → paṃsukuṇḍito (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | paṃsuguṇṭhito (pts2) | paṃsukuṇṭhito (mr)
msgctxt "sn9.1:4.1"
msgid "Sakuṇo yathā paṃsukunthito,"
msgstr "Just as a bird strewn with dirt"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:4.2"
msgid "Vidhunaṃ pātayati sitaṃ rajaṃ;"
msgstr "sheds that clingy dust with a shake;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ bhikkhu padhānavā satimā,"
msgstr "so too, an energetic, mindful mendicant"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.1:4.4"
msgid "Vidhunaṃ pātayati sitaṃ rajan”ti."
msgstr "sheds that clingy dust with a shake.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.1:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tāya devatāya saṃvejito saṃvegamāpādīti."
msgstr "Stirred up by that deity, that mendicant came to their senses."
